Few challenges have tested Kenyans’ collective resolve, resilience and resourcefulness in modern times than the Covid-19 pandemic. Families, teachers and education policymakers are unlikely to have a normal Christmas this year as they burn daylights and midnight oil, trying to figure out how to navigate school re-entry early after nearly a year of coronavirus disruption.



