However, Kenyans have manifested their customary determination not to turn over and die, but to confront emerging challenges with unyielding resolve.
Parents, school managers and policymakers are grappling with various options possible to kick-start the school calendar, but in compliance with the Ministry of Health protocols.
No one wishes to have school re-opening turn into super-spreader events like political rallies, parties and weddings. Specifically, social distancing requirements for schools have thrust the education sector into uncharted territory requiring a raft of infrastructural demands, including, but not limited to emergency construction of extra classrooms, dormitory spaces and recruitment of additional teachers to man the extra classes.



