Once political consultations and clarity on the role of each participant is secured, the delivery of the extra class rooms and dormitory facilities should take a shorter period and cost less than through normal disbursements of resources to schools, tendering processes, disputes that come with public procurement etc.
Polytechnics and technical schools have tendered for and executed public civil construction works in the past and have capacity for quick determination of Bills of Quantities , and human skills sets for quick execution if the military and NYS supplied materials at minimal non-commercial cost.
The national government has already taken a lead in this direction by setting aside resources for mass production of desks in response to the social distancing requirements ahead of reopening of schools.



